      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The App Store Connect API lets you create and configure auto-renewable subscriptions for your app. After you create an auto-renewable subscription, you can add metadata, such as a display name, description, and duration. You can also choose your subscription pricing, create promotional and introductory offers, and set up subscription offer codes. When your app is fully configured, you can submit your subscription for review. After you receive approval, you can make pricing changes and edit some metadata for your subscription.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Review-App-Store-Connect-API-usage",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Review App Store Connect API usage",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To manage auto-renewable subscriptions with the App Store Connect API, you need to understand key concepts for using the API. If youâ€™re new to using the App Store Connect API, make sure to read the documentation in the Essentials section of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.appstoreconnectapi/documentation/AppStoreConnectAPI",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and learn how to create API keys, generate JWTs, identify rate limits, and more.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To create and manage auto-renewable subscriptions, be sure you have one of the following user roles:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "ACCOUNT_HOLDER",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "ADMIN",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "code": "APP_MANAGER",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For the full list of App Store Connect user roles, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.appstoreconnectapi/documentation/AppStoreConnectAPI/UserRole",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/support/roles",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Plan-your-subscription-offerings",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Plan your subscription offerings",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Before you get started with creating your subscription, first identify which app to include this subscription in. To get the Apple ID of the app, use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GET /v1/apps",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.appstoreconnectapi/documentation/AppStoreConnectAPI/GET-v1-apps",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ") and search the resulting pages for the name of the app you want to use. In the response, make note of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "id",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " of that app, which appears in the following format:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "{",
            "\"data\" : [ {",
            "\"type\" : \"apps\",",
            "\"id\" : \"525463029\",",
            "...."
          ],
          "syntax": "other",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "You can also get the Apple ID of the app in App Store Connect.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Tip",
          "style": "tip",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To arrange your subscription groups, make sure to map out all your offerings clearly. The following table shows an example for planning your subscriptions in a subscription group. The example uses subscriptions for a series of ukulele lessons with different levels of instructor feedback and detail, available for various time periods.",
              "type": "text"
            }
